{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Dj1B6ZSxbshpJU6xiYcxaW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to test a specific user journey on http://localhost:8080. I need to:\n\n1. Navigate to http://localhost:8080\n2. Click on the first client name in the list\n3. Verify the page shows the client's name as a heading\n4. Verify there is a \"Back\" link or button\n5. Verify there are tabs or sections (Profile/Activity/Invoices)\n\nI should use the Playwright browser tools to do this. Let me start by navigating to the page and taking a snapshot to see what's there.\n\nThe steps are:\n1. Navigate to http://localhost:8080\n2. Click the first link in the table (client name)\n3. Verify client's name as heading\n4. Verify \"Back\" link/button\n5. Verify tabs or sections\n\nAt the end, I need to output a JSON with:\n- journey: \"View Client Profile\"\n- result: \"PASS\" or \"FAIL\"\n- steps_completed: number\n- steps_total: 5\n- notes: what happened\n\nLet me start.","signature":"